<HL>
   Business Brief -- Tektronix Inc.:
   Board Adopts `Poison Pill'
   To Deter Hostile Takeovers
</HL>
<DATE>
08/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7B
</SO>
<CO>
   TEK
</CO>
<LP>
   Tektronix Inc. said its board adopted a shareholder rights
plan aimed at discouraging unwanted takeovers.
   The "poison pill" plan would make any hostile takeover
attempt much more expensive. Tektronix said it didn't adopt
the plan in response to any specific threat.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Beaverton, Ore., electronics testing and measurements
concern has been plagued for years by stagnant sales and
dwindling margins. In May, it announced plans to lay of 1,300
workers and close down some business lines. For the fiscal
year ended May 26, it had a net loss of $92.6 million, or
$3.19 a share, on revenue of $1.4 billion.
</TEXT>
